history.content:
*priority given to first semester freshmen and junior transfers*
The Bioengineering Honor Society is very excited to be introducing our first ever Decal, Breaking Down BioE (BioE 98/198).

Breaking Down BioE bridges the BioE concentrations & courses on campus with the unique specialties of BioE such as Biomimetics, Computational Neuroengineering, and Orthopedic Bioengineering. If you would like to know more about the intersections of BioE with EECS, MSE and MCB through faculty & industry speakers, or gain insight into BioE electives through panels with BioEHS alumni & upperclassmen, apply to BioE 98/198! We have crafted this course to help you navigate what problems related to BioEECS you want to solve, and what resources on campus enable you to solve them. Starting next Thursday, this 2-unit course is open to students from all majors, and offers you exclusive access to BioEHS! Classes are Tu/Th, 7-8PM in 223 Dwinelle Hall.
